overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking validation against the provided Statement of Work and
  detailed questionnaire specification. The agent performed an in-depth analysis
  of the existing codebase, identifying several critical missing features and
  areas for enhancement. Subsequently, the agent proceeded with the
  implementation phase, focusing on high-priority items. Key additions included
  a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness interference, complete with safety
  warnings, and the integration of detection logic and recommendations for both
  Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome.
  Furthermore, the agent incorporated a dedicated "Resources & Next Steps"
  section with relevant external links and refined the Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness (EDS) scoring mechanism to include weighted activities. These
  changes involved updates across TypeScript types, validation schemas, and
  various React components responsible for the questionnaire UI and PDF report
  generation.
